<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Mapper #118 question]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11129&amp;p=127267#p127267"><![CDATA[
Due to how the board is wired, the register controlling CHR banking at $0000-$03ff also controls NT0 at $2000-$23ff, the register controlling CHR banking at $400-$7ff also controls NT1 at $2400-$27ff, and so on.<br /><br />If 'C' is clear, it just happens that the same register controls both CHR banking at $0000-$03ff and $400-$7ff, so the first two nametables, as well as the last 2, must be identical.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Sun Mar 30, 2014 3:13 am</p><hr />
